1. **Purpose**

A family member, Sarah who is an avid history buff and educator, requested for me to kindly create a mobile app for her, for her students. The purpose of the mobile app is to compare a user’s age to a famous historical figure. The historical application is meant to be educational for her students.

1. **Design considerations**

This is the design of the mobile application.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

“My Historical App” is the heading of the mobile application and it represents what the app is about. The image that you see above is the cover image of the mobile application, which also kind of gives a visual summary of what the app is about. The image displays the different historical figures I chose for this specific application. I made up this image with the images of the 10 historical figures I chose. “AGE” is a TextView and it is used to indicate to the user that they must enter a age that is between 20 and 100. “Generate History” is a button that is used to generate the historical figure and their age and give a short summary explaining what they were famous for. If there is no historical figure that matches the age entered by the user then it will display, “There is no Historical Figure identified that died at the age you entered. Try Again.”. If you entered a value that is below 20 or more than 100 then it will display, “Please enter a valid age between 20 and 100”. The “Clear” button is used to reset the app back to the start so that another user is able to enter a different age. The result box is used to display a short summary of the historical figure that matches the age you entered, and if there is no historical figure that matches the age you have entered, then in the result box it will display “There is no Historical Figure identified that died at the age you entered. Try Again.”.

- **Intuitive design**

The design of the mobile app is easy to follow and navigate from the top to the bottom, which will make the user be able to use the app without any complications. The design does not have a lot of products that are put in it, which makes it easier for the user to follow. The user will be able to successfully finish generating the History Mobile app without any complications or miscommunication.

- **Content prioritization**

The mobile app includes all the necessary aspects that were required from me to create the History Mobile Application. The app does not include unnecessary interface elements. The mobile app only displays essential content and functions that the user will need in order to be able to use the app, and so that it can run well.

- **Legible Text Content**

The app includes visible text for the user. The font is clear enough for the user to read and it is not complicated for the user to use. The text in the app is easily readable and the communication between the app and the user is very clear and quite simple. The text size used for the mobile application is 20sp for the title and 24sp for the “AGE” text view. The Diplomata font is used for the title of the mobile app for aesthetics.

- **Make Interface Elements Clearly Visible**

All the components displayed on the screen are viewed by the user clearly, even in the sunlight the brightness of the screen can be increased in order for the user to clearly see and be able to use the app and navigate what is needed.

- **Hand Position Controls**

The buttons are in a position where users will be able to easily navigate so that they are able to use the mobile application that is created. The buttons also accommodates the thumb’s reach zone perfectly, since most people use their one thumb to interact with their mobile phones.

- **Images**

The reason I used this image is to show the user the different historical figures that will be displayed if you enter your age that is similar to their age of death. The image is placed after the title of the mobile app to convey the message of the mobile app. The image I used for the cover page is made up of the different historical figures that I chose for this mobile application. The image I chose is pasted in the Drawable folder in my Android project.
